english_title: Sippin' Hennessy on the Ultimate High
content_vision: I'm not like others. I've been travelling my own path while others have been sheeps in the herd.
text:
Verse 1:
got my barbie and ken, we playin' house,
they always follow my lead, no doubt.
all my homies are invited, so let's go,
if you believe, we can take this show.
they try to tell us how to live, by the book that they think they read,
but we ain't followin' their rules, we got our own lead,
john sinclair, yeah we'll keep smokin', livin' how we please,
we don't care what they sayin', we'll do it with ease.

Pre-Chorus 1:
maybe we let go, time to break free,
they wanted heaven from me but i couldn't guarantee.

Chorus 1:
listen to the children, screaming in the street,
gotta let me run, to see who came undone, feeling the heat.
got them vibes down in la,
come on, girl, let's get that good sookie,

Verse 2:
and alright, i'm in the war room, feeling lost and low,
need to ask cupid, where did all my love go?
got a maid who does all the chores, so i don't have to lift a finger,
we ain't gonna stop living, just to appease the haters and linger.
in the party we da la, sippin' hennessy,
your eyes all lazy, but you make me feel good mentally.
and we walk a few miles, just to be where she is,
do you wanna take it there, show me that you're mine and hers?

Pre-Chorus 2:
on this windy road, twistin' and turnin', we don't know where we're gonna end
but we don't care, we just let it go, trustin' the journey we send

Chorus 2:
i'm tired of this power shit, it's overrated,
now i'm ready to rise again, leave my past faded.
riding by the water, feeling so fly,
like i'm parachuting on the ultimate high.

Chorus 3:
my boys always get whatever they need,
can't erase you from my thoughts, you're stuck in my mind like a weed.
niggas on me, ridin' round your side of town,
they thinkin' they can bring me down, but i won't drown.

Bridge:
my arms are reaching out for you,
'cause that's the physical, you're my desire.
they can't handle the real, just let it go and be free,
they keep watchin', but they don't gotta see,

Outro:
she taught me how to pimp my game up,
showed me the way, six hunnid, what's up?

Instrumental:
why you acting so distant, can't you see?
all these niggas 'bout to fall flat, that's where they'll be.

struct_suggs.name: The Rollercoaster Ride
attrs: short and snappy structure
keeps listeners engaged with the use of pre-choruses
builds anticipation for the chorus through the use of verses
has a satisfying ending with the final chorus

struct_suggs.name: The Instrumental Interlude
attrs: has a well-developed intro
utilizes varying pre-choruses and verses to keep the song interesting
introduces a bridge for added depth and change in the middle of the song
ends with a powerful final chorus in the outro

struct_suggs.name: The Dynamic Drop
attrs: includes a bridge early on in the song for added variety
keeps the chorus as the main focus and uses verses to support it
ends with a satisfying final chorus

struct_suggs.name: The Epic Adventure
attrs: has a longer intro that builds up and sets the tone for the song
utilizes a pre-chorus and chorus structure for the majority of the song
includes an interlude for a break and added musical element
finishes with a strong final chorus in the outro

struct_suggs.name: The Narrative Flow
attrs: keeps the focus on the verses and chorus, with a pre-chorus used only once
introduces a bridge and third chorus for added variety
has a strong and powerful ending with the final chorus in the outro

struct_suggs.name: The Musical Journey
attrs: has a shorter form and faster pace due to the lack of verses
uses pre-choruses to build anticipation for the chorus
incorporates an instrumental break to add diversity and showcase musical skills
has a satisfying ending with the final chorus

struct_suggs.name: The Winding Road
attrs: has a slightly different structure with the use of an interlude after the first chorus
utilizes a pre-chorus and chorus for each verse to build up to the bridge
adds depth and variety with the inclusion of an interlude and a bridge
ends with a powerful final chorus in the outro

struct_suggs.name: The Climactic Buildup
attrs: utilizes a more traditional structure with a verse and pre-chorus leading into a strong chorus
introduces a bridge and third chorus for added depth and variety
has an instrumental break to showcase musicianship
ends with a final chorus in the outro to wrap up the song

struct_suggs.name: The Energetic Collision
attrs: has a well-developed intro and uses verses and pre-choruses to build up to the chorus
includes a bridge early on in the song for added depth and variety
has a powerful final chorus in the outro
utilizes a more traditional structure with multiple verse-chorus repetitions

struct_suggs.name: The Rhythmic Ride
attrs: has a shorter form with a faster pace due to the lack of verses
keeps the focus on the chorus, with pre-choruses used to build anticipation
adds variety with the use of an interlude and bridge
has a satisfying ending with the final chorus in the outro.
